{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01U9bDrjwbLVyZuyecUedTXM","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-20 (Session 3)\n     2→\n     3→### 2-2-observability-hook-enforcement — dev-story AC3 fix (2026-03-20T06:18Z)\n     4→\n     5→- **`coverage-gate.ts` reads sprint-state.json twice:** Once via `readCoverageState()` for coverage numbers and once via `readCachedGaps()` for gap data. `ObservabilityCoverageState` type doesn't include gaps field — adding it would cascade. Acceptable for now.\n     6→- **No `codeharness analyze` command exists:** Changed all references to point to `codeharness observability-gate` or `patches/observability/` instead.\n     7→- **Gaps only populate after `saveCoverageResult` is called:** If sprint-state.json was written by older version without gaps field, gate returns empty gaps. Graceful degradation but means AC 3 only fully works after at least one analyzer run.\n     8→\n     9→### 2-2-observability-hook-enforcement — verify AC3 cycle (2026-03-20T06:28Z)\n    10→\n    11→- **All 3 ACs PASS** — black-box verification confirmed gap data flows end-to-end.\n    12→- **VictoriaLogs returned no events** — codeharness CLI doesn't emit OTEL data (expected — it instruments other projects, not itself).\n    13→- **pre-commit-gate.sh not in npm dist** — hook is a Claude Code plugin artifact, not packaged in npm tarball. Verifier correctly noted this and tested via the CLI command instead.\n    14→- **Stale container from prior session** — had to `docker rm -f` before starting. verify-env cleanup should handle this.\n    15→\n    16→### 2-2-observability-hook-enforcement — code-review AC3 cycle (2026-03-20T06:25Z)\n    17→\n    18→- **HIGH: Double file read in coverage-gate.ts** — `checkObservabilityCoverageGate()` read sprint-state.json twice independently (once for coverage, once for gaps). Fixed by adding gaps to StaticCoverageState and parsing in extractCoverageState().\n    19→- **HIGH: Gaps never parsed back through readCoverageState** — StaticCoverageState lacked gaps field, so AC 3 always showed empty. Root cause of the verify failure. Fixed.\n    20→- **MEDIUM: Fix suggestion referenced generic patches/ path** — changed to reference actual codeharness observability-gate command.\n    21→- **LOW (not fixed): Duplicated default target constants** in coverage.ts and coverage-gate.ts.\n    22→- **LOW (not fixed): No integration test for full gap flow** (write state → run gate → verify gaps appear).\n    23→\n    24→---\n    25→\n    26→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-20 (Session 2)\n    27→\n    28→### 2-2-observability-hook-enforcement — verify (2026-03-20T06:10Z)\n    29→\n    30→- **AC 3 FAIL: `gapSummary` hardcoded as empty array** — `checkObservabilityCoverageGate()` never reads gap data from sprint-state.json or calls analyzer. The formatting code exists but has no data to display.\n    31→- **No `codeharness analyze` CLI command** — block message references it but command doesn't exist.\n    32→- **AC 1 and AC 2 PASS** — basic gate behavior works correctly.\n    33→- **VictoriaLogs returned no events** — CLI doesn't emit OTEL data (expected for a tool that instruments other projects).\n    34→- Returning to dev for AC 3 fix.\n    35→\n    36→### 2-2-observability-hook-enforcement — code-review (2026-03-20T06:15Z)\n    37→\n    38→- **HIGH: `saveCoverageResult` dropped `runtime` field** — every `codeharness analyze` run wiped runtime coverage data from sprint-state.json. Fixed.\n    39→- **HIGH: No NaN validation on `--min-static`/`--min-runtime`** — `parseInt` with non-numeric input silently set NaN target, gate always failed with no error. Fixed.\n    40→- **HIGH: `timeout` command not on stock macOS** — observability gate check silently never ran on Mac. Fixed by removing `timeout`.\n    41→- **MEDIUM: AGENTS.md files not updated** — coverage-gate.ts and observability-gate.ts missing from module docs. Fixed.\n    42→- **LOW (not fixed): Grep-based JSON parsing in pre-commit-gate.sh** — fragile, pre-existing pattern.\n    43→- **LOW (not fixed): Unreachable DEFAULT_STATIC_TARGET fallback** — dead defensive code.\n    44→\n    45→### 2-2-observability-hook-enforcement — dev-story (2026-03-20T06:00Z)\n    46→\n    47→- **Pre-existing BATS failures:** 4 tests in `tests/integration/hooks.bats` (tests 28-31) fail on master — `hooks.json` format mismatch. Not caused by this story.\n    48→- **`extractCoverageState` was incomplete:** Existing function didn't parse `runtime` section or `runtimeTarget` from sprint-state.json, even though Story 2.1 writes runtime data. Extended it — technically a bug fix for Story 2.1.\n    49→- **Gap details limited in hook:** Hook directs users to run `codeharness analyze` instead of showing file/line details (Semgrep too slow for hook context).\n    50→- **sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent** — updated manually by harness-run.\n    51→\n    52→### 2-2-observability-hook-enforcement — create-story (2026-03-20T05:50Z)\n    53→\n    54→- **Ambiguity in AC 3:** Epic says block message should include specific files/functions missing logging. Getting specific gaps requires running Semgrep (~10s), violating 500ms hook NFR. Story resolves by using cached coverage and directing user to `codeharness analyze`.\n    55→- **Risk: `coverage.ts` line limit.** Existing file is 269 lines; adding gate function (~40 lines) may exceed 300-line NFR9 limit.\n    56→- **No `codeharness analyze` CLI command exists yet.** Story references it in error messages but no such subcommand exists. Dev needs to create it or adjust messaging.\n    57→- **sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent** — updated manually by harness-run.\n    58→\n    59→### 2-1-verification-observability-check — create-story (2026-03-19T09:00Z)\n    60→\n    61→- **Epic 0.5 appeared:** The create-story agent added a new Epic 0.5 (Stream-JSON Live Activity Display) to sprint-status.yaml despite being told not to modify it. This is a workflow compliance issue.\n    62→- **AC #1 integration risk:** Verifying that the verifier queries observability after docker exec requires a live verification session — hard to test in isolation.\n    63→- **Tag coupling risk:** `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tag format is a convention between prompt template and parser regex. If verifier (Claude) doesn't emit exact format, parser won't detect it.\n    64→- **Naming confusion:** Epic 2 retrospective file references a different Epic 2 from a previous sprint.\n    65→\n    66→### 2-1-verification-observability-check — dev-story (2026-03-19T09:08Z)\n    67→\n    68→- **Import boundary violation (fixed):** `runtime-coverage.ts` initially imported from `../verify/types.js` directly. Fixed to use barrel import.\n    69→- **logEventCount is binary:** Set to 0 or 1 based on gap presence, not actual log event count. Parser only detects `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tag presence.\n    70→- **VerifyResult field additions are breaking:** All existing `VerifyResult` constructions needed updating (5 files). Optional fields with defaults would reduce churn.\n    71→- **Task 2.4 no-op:** No new config fields needed — existing `observabilityEndpoints.victoriaLogs` already sufficient.\n    72→\n    73→### 2-1-verification-observability-check — code-review (2026-03-19T09:15Z)\n    74→\n    75→- **HIGH: saveRuntimeCoverage was dead code** — never called from production, only tested. Runtime coverage would never persist to sprint-state.json. Fixed.\n    76→- **MEDIUM: verify.ts hardcoded 0 gaps** — command always reported 0 observability gaps regardless of proof content. Fixed.\n    77→- **MEDIUM: verifier-session.ts hardcoded 0 gaps** — same pattern as verify.ts. Fixed.\n    78→- **LOW (not fixed): Binary logEventCount** — always 0 or 1, not actual log counts. Tech debt.\n    79→- **LOW (not fixed): Duplicated coverage math** — verify/index.ts duplicates computeRuntimeCoverage logic.\n    80→- **LOW (not fixed): Silent catch blocks** — gap parsing errors silently swallowed in 3 locations.\n    81→- **Architecture: Hardcoded CWD** — verifyStory() calls saveRuntimeCoverage with '.' as projectDir, assumes CWD is project root.\n    82→- **Architecture: Triple gap parsing** — 3 separate locations independently parse gaps. Should be centralized.\n    83→\n    84→### 2-1-verification-observability-check — verify (2026-03-20T05:40Z)\n    85→\n    86→- **Proof markdown parsing bug:** Verifier embedded a heredoc containing nested code fences (````bash`/````output`) inside a bash code block. The closing backticks broke out of the outer fence, causing `## AC N: PASS` headings from the test proof to appear as real AC sections. The proof parser counted 8 ACs instead of 4. Fixed by summarizing the heredoc content.\n    87→- **Evidence adjacency requirement:** The proof parser requires `bash` and `output` code blocks to be adjacent (no text between them). AC3 had explanatory text between the blocks, causing it to be counted as pending. Fixed by removing the intervening text.\n    88→- **VictoriaLogs zero events:** The codeharness CLI does not emit OpenTelemetry data in the Docker container, so all observability gap checks return empty. This is expected for a tool that instruments other projects, not itself.\n    89→- **AC1 template verification limitation:** The verify-prompt.ts template compiles into the Claude Code plugin (skills/), not the npm CLI binary. Cannot directly inspect the template from Docker. Verified via the template-to-parser contract (OBSERVABILITY_GAP_TAG constant, parseObservabilityGaps function, verify --json output fields).\n    90→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c5eaf6a6-ac7c-4707-b82c-6220d711aa9c","uuid":"4f705995-bcc9-49a7-b471-268f6c0d8757","timestamp":"2026-03-20T06:32:47.904Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-20 (Session 3)\n\n### 2-2-observability-hook-enforcement — dev-story AC3 fix (2026-03-20T06:18Z)\n\n- **`coverage-gate.ts` reads sprint-state.json twice:** Once via `readCoverageState()` for coverage numbers and once via `readCachedGaps()` for gap data. `ObservabilityCoverageState` type doesn't include gaps field — adding it would cascade. Acceptable for now.\n- **No `codeharness analyze` command exists:** Changed all references to point to `codeharness observability-gate` or `patches/observability/` instead.\n- **Gaps only populate after `saveCoverageResult` is called:** If sprint-state.json was written by older version without gaps field, gate returns empty gaps. Graceful degradation but means AC 3 only fully works after at least one analyzer run.\n\n### 2-2-observability-hook-enforcement — verify AC3 cycle (2026-03-20T06:28Z)\n\n- **All 3 ACs PASS** — black-box verification confirmed gap data flows end-to-end.\n- **VictoriaLogs returned no events** — codeharness CLI doesn't emit OTEL data (expected — it instruments other projects, not itself).\n- **pre-commit-gate.sh not in npm dist** — hook is a Claude Code plugin artifact, not packaged in npm tarball. Verifier correctly noted this and tested via the CLI command instead.\n- **Stale container from prior session** — had to `docker rm -f` before starting. verify-env cleanup should handle this.\n\n### 2-2-observability-hook-enforcement — code-review AC3 cycle (2026-03-20T06:25Z)\n\n- **HIGH: Double file read in coverage-gate.ts** — `checkObservabilityCoverageGate()` read sprint-state.json twice independently (once for coverage, once for gaps). Fixed by adding gaps to StaticCoverageState and parsing in extractCoverageState().\n- **HIGH: Gaps never parsed back through readCoverageState** — StaticCoverageState lacked gaps field, so AC 3 always showed empty. Root cause of the verify failure. Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM: Fix suggestion referenced generic patches/ path** — changed to reference actual codeharness observability-gate command.\n- **LOW (not fixed): Duplicated default target constants** in coverage.ts and coverage-gate.ts.\n- **LOW (not fixed): No integration test for full gap flow** (write state → run gate → verify gaps appear).\n\n---\n\n# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-20 (Session 2)\n\n### 2-2-observability-hook-enforcement — verify (2026-03-20T06:10Z)\n\n- **AC 3 FAIL: `gapSummary` hardcoded as empty array** — `checkObservabilityCoverageGate()` never reads gap data from sprint-state.json or calls analyzer. The formatting code exists but has no data to display.\n- **No `codeharness analyze` CLI command** — block message references it but command doesn't exist.\n- **AC 1 and AC 2 PASS** — basic gate behavior works correctly.\n- **VictoriaLogs returned no events** — CLI doesn't emit OTEL data (expected for a tool that instruments other projects).\n- Returning to dev for AC 3 fix.\n\n### 2-2-observability-hook-enforcement — code-review (2026-03-20T06:15Z)\n\n- **HIGH: `saveCoverageResult` dropped `runtime` field** — every `codeharness analyze` run wiped runtime coverage data from sprint-state.json. Fixed.\n- **HIGH: No NaN validation on `--min-static`/`--min-runtime`** — `parseInt` with non-numeric input silently set NaN target, gate always failed with no error. Fixed.\n- **HIGH: `timeout` command not on stock macOS** — observability gate check silently never ran on Mac. Fixed by removing `timeout`.\n- **MEDIUM: AGENTS.md files not updated** — coverage-gate.ts and observability-gate.ts missing from module docs. Fixed.\n- **LOW (not fixed): Grep-based JSON parsing in pre-commit-gate.sh** — fragile, pre-existing pattern.\n- **LOW (not fixed): Unreachable DEFAULT_STATIC_TARGET fallback** — dead defensive code.\n\n### 2-2-observability-hook-enforcement — dev-story (2026-03-20T06:00Z)\n\n- **Pre-existing BATS failures:** 4 tests in `tests/integration/hooks.bats` (tests 28-31) fail on master — `hooks.json` format mismatch. Not caused by this story.\n- **`extractCoverageState` was incomplete:** Existing function didn't parse `runtime` section or `runtimeTarget` from sprint-state.json, even though Story 2.1 writes runtime data. Extended it — technically a bug fix for Story 2.1.\n- **Gap details limited in hook:** Hook directs users to run `codeharness analyze` instead of showing file/line details (Semgrep too slow for hook context).\n- **sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent** — updated manually by harness-run.\n\n### 2-2-observability-hook-enforcement — create-story (2026-03-20T05:50Z)\n\n- **Ambiguity in AC 3:** Epic says block message should include specific files/functions missing logging. Getting specific gaps requires running Semgrep (~10s), violating 500ms hook NFR. Story resolves by using cached coverage and directing user to `codeharness analyze`.\n- **Risk: `coverage.ts` line limit.** Existing file is 269 lines; adding gate function (~40 lines) may exceed 300-line NFR9 limit.\n- **No `codeharness analyze` CLI command exists yet.** Story references it in error messages but no such subcommand exists. Dev needs to create it or adjust messaging.\n- **sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent** — updated manually by harness-run.\n\n### 2-1-verification-observability-check — create-story (2026-03-19T09:00Z)\n\n- **Epic 0.5 appeared:** The create-story agent added a new Epic 0.5 (Stream-JSON Live Activity Display) to sprint-status.yaml despite being told not to modify it. This is a workflow compliance issue.\n- **AC #1 integration risk:** Verifying that the verifier queries observability after docker exec requires a live verification session — hard to test in isolation.\n- **Tag coupling risk:** `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tag format is a convention between prompt template and parser regex. If verifier (Claude) doesn't emit exact format, parser won't detect it.\n- **Naming confusion:** Epic 2 retrospective file references a different Epic 2 from a previous sprint.\n\n### 2-1-verification-observability-check — dev-story (2026-03-19T09:08Z)\n\n- **Import boundary violation (fixed):** `runtime-coverage.ts` initially imported from `../verify/types.js` directly. Fixed to use barrel import.\n- **logEventCount is binary:** Set to 0 or 1 based on gap presence, not actual log event count. Parser only detects `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tag presence.\n- **VerifyResult field additions are breaking:** All existing `VerifyResult` constructions needed updating (5 files). Optional fields with defaults would reduce churn.\n- **Task 2.4 no-op:** No new config fields needed — existing `observabilityEndpoints.victoriaLogs` already sufficient.\n\n### 2-1-verification-observability-check — code-review (2026-03-19T09:15Z)\n\n- **HIGH: saveRuntimeCoverage was dead code** — never called from production, only tested. Runtime coverage would never persist to sprint-state.json. Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM: verify.ts hardcoded 0 gaps** — command always reported 0 observability gaps regardless of proof content. Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM: verifier-session.ts hardcoded 0 gaps** — same pattern as verify.ts. Fixed.\n- **LOW (not fixed): Binary logEventCount** — always 0 or 1, not actual log counts. Tech debt.\n- **LOW (not fixed): Duplicated coverage math** — verify/index.ts duplicates computeRuntimeCoverage logic.\n- **LOW (not fixed): Silent catch blocks** — gap parsing errors silently swallowed in 3 locations.\n- **Architecture: Hardcoded CWD** — verifyStory() calls saveRuntimeCoverage with '.' as projectDir, assumes CWD is project root.\n- **Architecture: Triple gap parsing** — 3 separate locations independently parse gaps. Should be centralized.\n\n### 2-1-verification-observability-check — verify (2026-03-20T05:40Z)\n\n- **Proof markdown parsing bug:** Verifier embedded a heredoc containing nested code fences (````bash`/````output`) inside a bash code block. The closing backticks broke out of the outer fence, causing `## AC N: PASS` headings from the test proof to appear as real AC sections. The proof parser counted 8 ACs instead of 4. Fixed by summarizing the heredoc content.\n- **Evidence adjacency requirement:** The proof parser requires `bash` and `output` code blocks to be adjacent (no text between them). AC3 had explanatory text between the blocks, causing it to be counted as pending. Fixed by removing the intervening text.\n- **VictoriaLogs zero events:** The codeharness CLI does not emit OpenTelemetry data in the Docker container, so all observability gap checks return empty. This is expected for a tool that instruments other projects, not itself.\n- **AC1 template verification limitation:** The verify-prompt.ts template compiles into the Claude Code plugin (skills/), not the npm CLI binary. Cannot directly inspect the template from Docker. Verified via the template-to-parser contract (OBSERVABILITY_GAP_TAG constant, parseObservabilityGaps function, verify --json output fields).\n","numLines":90,"startLine":1,"totalLines":90}}}
