ude.\"\n- **Risk: AC 1 is hard to verify in isolation.** It requires a running VictoriaLogs instance, OTLP-instrumented test suite, and test execution producing telemetry. Tagged as `integration-required`. The unit tests will mock all of this, but black-box verification needs the full stack.\n- **Observation: 2-2 verification findings.** Story 2-2 has an open AC 3 failure (empty gapSummary). The dev notes for 2-3 mention this so the developer doesn't repeat the pattern.\n- **Risk: Module detection heuristic.** The architecture says \"module-level matching\" for runtime coverage but doesn't specify how to discover modules or map telemetry events to them. The story defines a source-directory-scanning approach, but this is an assumption -- the architecture leaves it unspecified.\n- **Workaround: No config.yaml found at expected path.** The workflow references `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` but the actual config is at `_bmad/config.yaml`. Used the actual path."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ad6d9b629d3a16f06 (use SendMessage with to: 'ad6d9b629d3a16f06' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 68332\ntool_uses: 33\nduration_ms: 211389</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c5eaf6a6-ac7c-4707-b82c-6220d711aa9c","uuid":"bd32c3c4-3825-42c9-90fd-7f93bd4dcec8","timestamp":"2026-03-20T06:36:44.226Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /create-story for story 2-3-standalone-runtime-check-audit-mode. The sprint-status.yaml is at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml. Auto-discover the next backlog story and create it. For each AC, append `<!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->` or `<!-- verification: integration-required -->` based on whether the AC can be verified by running CLI commands in a subprocess. ACs referencing workflows, sprint planning, user sessions, or external system interactions should be tagged as integration-required. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run 