{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Bo5Vj6FRQG4oyWWUjGNBS9","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Observability Module\n     2→\n     3→Static analysis of observability coverage (logging gaps, error handler coverage) and coverage state tracking over time.\n     4→\n     5→## Files\n     6→\n     7→- `index.ts` — Public API barrel: re-exports `analyze` from analyzer, `saveCoverageResult`, `readCoverageState`, `getCoverageTrend`, `checkCoverageTarget` from coverage, and all public types.\n     8→- `analyzer.ts` — Static analysis runner: `analyze(projectDir, config?)` — runs Semgrep (or skips gracefully if not installed), parses results into tool-agnostic `AnalyzerResult`. Also exports `checkSemgrepInstalled`, `runSemgrep`, `parseSemgrepOutput`, `computeSummary`.\n     9→- `coverage.ts` — Coverage state persistence: `saveCoverageResult(projectDir, result)` — writes coverage to sprint-state.json atomically, appends to history. `readCoverageState(projectDir)` — reads typed coverage state. `getCoverageTrend(projectDir)` — compares latest vs previous history entry. `checkCoverageTarget(projectDir, target?)` — checks coverage against target (default 80%).\n    10→- `coverage-gate.ts` — Commit gate check: `checkObservabilityCoverageGate(projectDir, overrides?)` — reads cached static and runtime coverage from sprint-state.json, compares against targets. Does NOT re-run Semgrep. Static is always required; runtime only checked when data exists. Returns `ObservabilityCoverageGateResult`.\n    11→- `runtime-coverage.ts` — Runtime coverage persistence: `computeRuntimeCoverage(gaps, totalACs)` — computes runtime coverage from verification observability gaps. `saveRuntimeCoverage(projectDir, result)` — writes runtime coverage to sprint-state.json atomically.\n    12→- `types.ts` — All interfaces: `AnalyzerResult`, `AnalyzerConfig`, `AnalyzerSummary`, `ObservabilityGap`, `GapSeverity`, `SemgrepRawOutput`, `SemgrepResult`, `ObservabilityCoverageState`, `StaticCoverageState`, `CoverageTargets`, `CoverageHistoryEntry`, `CoverageTrend`, `CoverageTargetResult`, `ObservabilityCoverageGateResult`, `RuntimeCoverageEntry`, `RuntimeCoverageResult`, `RuntimeCoverageState`.\n    13→\n    14→## Patterns\n    15→\n    16→- All public functions return `Result<T>` (never throw)\n    17→- Atomic writes via temp file + `renameSync` (same pattern as sprint/state.ts)\n    18→- ES module imports with `.js` extensions\n    19→- Coverage state stored in `sprint-state.json` under `observability` key\n    20→- Static and runtime coverage tracked separately (architecture Decision 2)\n    21→- Gate checks use cached state only — no Semgrep re-runs in hooks for performance\n    22→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014QEC8wgRDzeoWECp9trCxd","session_id":"c5eaf6a6-ac7c-4707-b82c-6220d711aa9c","uuid":"ff5c57a7-6ca8-458e-ada6-404280591ade","timestamp":"2026-03-20T06:37:48.996Z"}
