{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013RMt8joSVQ4L6gPhzY2THS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 2.3: Standalone Runtime Check (Audit Mode)\n     2→\n     3→Status: review\n     4→\n     5→<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     6→\n     7→## Story\n     8→\n     9→As an operator,\n    10→I want runtime observability checked outside of verification,\n    11→so that `codeharness audit` can validate telemetry without full Docker verification.\n    12→\n    13→## Acceptance Criteria\n    14→\n    15→1. **Given** `codeharness audit` runs, **When** OTLP is enabled and tests run, **Then** the observability backend is queried for telemetry events during the test window. <!-- verification: integration-required -->\n    16→2. **Given** 8 modules in the project and 5 emitted telemetry, **When** reported, **Then** runtime coverage = 62.5% with the 3 silent modules listed. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→3. **Given** the observability stack is not running, **When** the runtime check runs, **Then** it reports \"runtime validation skipped -- observability stack not available\" as a warning, not a hard failure. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→\n    19→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    20→\n    21→- [x] Task 1: Define runtime-validator types in `src/modules/observability/types.ts` (AC: #1, #2)\n    22→  - [x] 1.1: Add `RuntimeValidationConfig` interface with fields: `testCommand: string` (default `npm test`), `otlpEndpoint: string`, `queryEndpoint: string`, `timeoutMs: number` (default 120000)\n    23→  - [x] 1.2: Add `ModuleTelemetryEntry` interface with fields: `moduleName: string`, `telemetryDetected: boolean`, `eventCount: number`\n    24→  - [x] 1.3: Add `RuntimeValidationResult` interface with fields: `entries: ModuleTelemetryEntry[]`, `totalModules: number`, `modulesWithTelemetry: number`, `coveragePercent: number`, `skipped: boolean`, `skipReason?: string`\n    25→  - [x] 1.4: Export new types from `src/modules/observability/index.ts`\n    26→\n    27→- [x] Task 2: Implement runtime validator in `src/modules/observability/runtime-validator.ts` (AC: #1, #2, #3)\n    28→  - [x] 2.1: Implement `validateRuntime(projectDir: string, config?: Partial<RuntimeValidationConfig>): Result<RuntimeValidationResult>` that:\n    29→    1. Checks if observability backend is reachable (health check on query endpoint)\n    30→    2. If unreachable, returns skipped result with reason \"runtime validation skipped -- observability stack not available\"\n    31→    3. Records a timestamp before running tests\n    32→    4. Spawns `config.testCommand` (default `npm test`) with `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT` env var set\n    33→    5. After tests complete, queries the observability backend for telemetry events in the time window\n    34→    6. Maps telemetry events to modules (by source file path prefix or service name)\n    35→    7. Computes module-level coverage: modulesWithTelemetry / totalModules * 100\n    36→  - [x] 2.2: Implement `checkBackendHealth(queryEndpoint: string): boolean` -- simple HTTP GET to the health endpoint, returns true if 2xx response within 3 seconds\n    37→  - [x] 2.3: Implement `queryTelemetryEvents(queryEndpoint: string, startTime: string, endTime: string): Result<TelemetryEvent[]>` -- queries VictoriaLogs for events in window\n    38→  - [x] 2.4: Implement `mapEventsToModules(events: TelemetryEvent[], projectDir: string): ModuleTelemetryEntry[]` -- groups events by module name (derived from source path or service attribute)\n    39→  - [x] 2.5: Keep file under 200 lines\n    40→\n    41→- [x] Task 3: Persist runtime validation results to state (AC: #2)\n    42→  - [x] 3.1: Reuse `saveRuntimeCoverage` from `runtime-coverage.ts` or create a parallel `saveRuntimeValidation` if the shape differs\n    43→  - [x] 3.2: Runtime validation results write to `sprint-state.json` under `observability.runtime` (same location as verification-based runtime coverage, per Decision 2)\n    44→  - [x] 3.3: Include module-level details in state for audit reporting: `observability.runtime.modules: ModuleTelemetryEntry[]`\n    45→\n    46→- [x] Task 4: Export runtime validator from barrel (AC: all)\n    47→  - [x] 4.1: Add `validateRuntime` export to `src/modules/observability/index.ts`\n    48→  - [x] 4.2: Add new type exports: `RuntimeValidationConfig`, `ModuleTelemetryEntry`, `RuntimeValidationResult`\n    49→\n    50→- [x] Task 5: Write unit tests (AC: all)\n    51→  - [x] 5.1: Create `src/modules/observability/__tests__/runtime-validator.test.ts`:\n    52→    - Test `validateRuntime` returns skipped result when backend health check fails (AC #3)\n    53→    - Test `validateRuntime` runs tests and queries backend when healthy (AC #1)\n    54→    - Test coverage computation: 5/8 modules = 62.5% (AC #2)\n    55→    - Test silent modules are listed in result entries (AC #2)\n    56→    - Test coverage = 0% when no modules emit telemetry\n    57→    - Test coverage = 100% when all modules emit telemetry\n    58→    - Test custom config overrides (test command, endpoints)\n    59→  - [x] 5.2: Mock all I/O: HTTP requests, subprocess execution, filesystem\n    60→  - [x] 5.3: Mock `checkBackendHealth` to return true/false for different test cases\n    61→  - [x] 5.4: Target 100% coverage on all new files\n    62→\n    63→- [x] Task 6: Integration verification (AC: all)\n    64→  - [x] 6.1: Run `npm run build` -- verify tsup compiles new module\n    65→  - [x] 6.2: Run `npm run test:unit` -- all tests pass\n    66→  - [x] 6.3: Verify module boundaries: only barrel index.ts exports public API\n    67→  - [x] 6.4: Verify no file exceeds 300 lines (NFR9)\n    68→\n    69→## Dev Notes\n    70→\n    71→### Architecture References\n    72→\n    73→This story implements FR9 (standalone runtime check via tests with OTLP enabled) and extends the runtime observability coverage capability from Story 2.1 to work outside of Docker verification.\n    74→\n    75→Architecture Decision 3 (Runtime Validation) defines the standalone approach: run `npm test` with OTLP enabled, query observability backend for events, report module-level coverage. This is the fallback for projects not going through full verification.\n    76→\n    77→Architecture Decision 2 (Separate Metrics) applies: runtime coverage from this standalone check is stored in the same `observability.runtime` section as verification-based runtime coverage.\n    78→\n    79→### Key Implementation Details\n    80→\n    81→**Standalone vs. verification runtime:** Story 2.1 computes runtime coverage from `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tags in proof documents during Docker verification. This story (2.3) provides an alternative path: run tests locally with OTLP tracing enabled, then query the observability backend for telemetry events. Both paths write to the same `observability.runtime` state section.\n    82→\n    83→**Module detection strategy:** The runtime validator discovers project modules by scanning `src/` directories (or configured source roots). After tests run, it queries VictoriaLogs for events where the source/service attribute matches each module prefix. A module \"has telemetry\" if at least one log/trace/metric event was emitted from code within that module during the test window.\n    84→\n    85→**Observability backend query:** Use the same VictoriaLogs endpoint from the verify-prompt config. Query format:\n    86→```\n    87→curl '${victoriaLogs}/select/logsql/query?query=_stream_id:*&start=${startTime}&end=${endTime}&limit=1000'\n    88→```\n    89→The start/end times bracket the test execution window.\n    90→\n    91→**Health check before test run:** Before spawning the test process, check if the observability backend is reachable. If not, return a warning-level skip result rather than failing the entire audit. This prevents `codeharness audit` from failing when the observability stack is not running.\n    92→\n    93→**Test command configuration:** Default is `npm test`. Projects can override via config (e.g., `pytest`, `go test ./...`). The test command is spawned with `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT` set to the configured OTLP endpoint so telemetry is emitted during tests.\n    94→\n    95→**No CLI command in this story:** This story implements the module-level function `validateRuntime()` that will be called by the audit coordinator (Epic 3, Story 3.1). No new CLI subcommand is needed here -- the audit command will orchestrate calling this.\n    96→\n    97→### Existing Code to Reuse\n    98→\n    99→- `src/modules/observability/runtime-coverage.ts` -- `saveRuntimeCoverage()` for persisting results to `sprint-state.json`\n   100→- `src/modules/observability/coverage.ts` -- `readCoverageState()` for reading current state\n   101→- `src/modules/observability/types.ts` -- `RuntimeCoverageState`, `ObservabilityCoverageState` for state shape\n   102→- `src/modules/observability/index.ts` -- barrel to update with new exports\n   103→- `src/types/result.ts` -- `Result<T>` pattern used by all modules\n   104→- `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts` -- VictoriaLogs endpoint format (reference for query construction)\n   105→\n   106→### What This Story Does NOT Include\n   107→\n   108→- No new CLI subcommand -- this is a module function, not a user-facing command (audit command is Epic 3)\n   109→- No Docker verification integration -- that's Story 2.1 (already done)\n   110→- No hook enforcement of runtime coverage -- that's Story 2.2 (already done)\n   111→- No audit coordinator calling this function -- that's Story 3.1\n   112→- No combined static+runtime metric -- metrics are always separate (Decision 2)\n   113→- No OpenSearch backend support in this story -- VictoriaLogs only; OpenSearch adapter is a future enhancement\n   114→\n   115→### Dependencies\n   116→\n   117→- **Depends on:** Story 2.1 (runtime coverage types, `saveRuntimeCoverage`) -- DONE\n   118→- **Depends on:** Story 1.3 (coverage state persistence pattern) -- DONE\n   119→- **Depended on by:** Story 3.1 (audit coordinator calls `validateRuntime`), Story 5.2 (verification runtime integration)\n   120→\n   121→### File Size Constraint\n   122→\n   123→Each new file must be under 300 lines per NFR9. `runtime-validator.ts` should be ~150-180 lines. Types additions should be ~30 lines.\n   124→\n   125→### Previous Story Intelligence (Story 2.2)\n   126→\n   127→- **Cached state, not re-analysis:** Story 2.2's hook reads cached coverage from `sprint-state.json` instead of re-running Semgrep for performance. This story writes to the same state location, so the hook will automatically pick up runtime coverage from standalone checks.\n   128→- **Barrel imports only:** Story 2.1 had a bug importing from `../verify/types.js` instead of `../verify/index.js`. Always import from barrel.\n   129→- **Atomic write pattern:** Use read-modify-write with temp+rename for any state file updates.\n   130→- **Mock all I/O:** All filesystem and network operations mocked in unit tests. No real HTTP calls or file reads.\n   131→- **AC 3 gap detail bug in 2.2:** `checkObservabilityCoverageGate()` returned empty `gapSummary`. When implementing this story, ensure the result includes actual module entries -- not empty arrays.\n   132→- **File under 150 lines ideal:** `runtime-coverage.ts` is 112 lines. Keep `runtime-validator.ts` similarly lean if possible (though HTTP + subprocess + query logic may push to ~180).\n   133→\n   134→### References\n   135→\n   136→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md#Decision 2] -- Separate metrics, same state location\n   137→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md#Decision 3] -- Runtime Validation, standalone audit mode approach\n   138→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md#Decision 6] -- Module structure, runtime-validator.ts placement\n   139→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-operational-excellence.md#Story 2.3] -- Acceptance criteria and user story\n   140→- [Source: src/modules/observability/runtime-coverage.ts] -- saveRuntimeCoverage, atomic write pattern\n   141→- [Source: src/modules/observability/types.ts] -- RuntimeCoverageState, ObservabilityCoverageState\n   142→- [Source: src/modules/observability/coverage-gate.ts] -- Gate check reading cached state\n   143→- [Source: src/templates/verify-prompt.ts] -- VictoriaLogs query format reference\n   144→\n   145→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n   146→## Verification Requirements\n   147→\n   148→- [ ] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/2-3-standalone-runtime-check-audit-mode.proof.md`)\n   149→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n   150→- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100% of all new code in src/)\n   151→\n   152→## Documentation Requirements\n   153→\n   154→- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (src/modules/observability/AGENTS.md)\n   155→- [ ] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/2-3-standalone-runtime-check-audit-mode.md`\n   156→\n   157→## Testing Requirements\n   158→\n   159→- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n   160→- [ ] HTTP and subprocess operations mocked (no real I/O in unit tests)\n   161→- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n   162→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n   163→\n   164→## Dev Agent Record\n   165→\n   166→### Agent Model Used\n   167→\n   168→Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n   169→\n   170→### Debug Log References\n   171→\n   172→### Completion Notes List\n   173→\n   174→- Implemented `validateRuntime()` with health check, test execution, backend query, and module-level coverage computation\n   175→- Added 4 new types: `RuntimeValidationConfig`, `ModuleTelemetryEntry`, `RuntimeValidationResult`, `TelemetryEvent`\n   176→- Created 31 unit tests covering all ACs: skipped result on unhealthy backend (AC#3), test+query flow (AC#1), 62.5% coverage computation with silent modules listed (AC#2)\n   177→- All I/O mocked: fetch (HTTP), execSync (subprocess), readdirSync/statSync (filesystem)\n   178→- `runtime-validator.ts` is exactly 200 lines (under 200-line story target, under 300-line NFR9 limit)\n   179→- `types.ts` is 293 lines (under 300-line NFR9 limit)\n   180→- Task 3 (state persistence): `validateRuntime()` returns `RuntimeValidationResult` whose shape is compatible with `saveRuntimeCoverage()`. The caller (audit coordinator, Story 3.1) will persist via existing `saveRuntimeCoverage()`. No separate persistence function was needed since the shapes align.\n   181→- Full test suite: 2656 tests pass, 0 regressions\n   182→- Build succeeds with tsup\n   183→\n   184→### Change Log\n   185→\n   186→- 2026-03-20: Implemented Story 2.3 — standalone runtime validator for audit mode\n   187→\n   188→### File List\n   189→\n   190→- src/modules/observability/types.ts (modified — added RuntimeValidationConfig, ModuleTelemetryEntry, RuntimeValidationResult, TelemetryEvent)\n   191→- src/modules/observability/runtime-validator.ts (new — validateRuntime, checkBackendHealth, queryTelemetryEvents, mapEventsToModules)\n   192→- src/modules/observability/index.ts (modified — added new type and function exports)\n   193→- src/modules/observability/AGENTS.md (modified — added runtime-validator.ts documentation)\n   194→- src/modules/observability/__tests__/runtime-validator.test.ts (new — 31 tests)\n   195→- docs/exec-plans/active/2-3-standalone-runtime-check-audit-mode.md (new — exec plan)\n   196→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01X8HPzdvjqKbRcjmtsWDTRD","session_id":"c5eaf6a6-ac7c-4707-b82c-6220d711aa9c","uuid":"9199adba-061b-4d3c-ab83-b33f1d2dd6ea","timestamp":"2026-03-20T06:44:41.758Z"}
