{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01X8HPzdvjqKbRcjmtsWDTRD","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is the summary of what was done:\n\n**Adversarial review completed** on Story 2.3 (standalone runtime validator). Found and fixed 4 issues (3 HIGH, 1 MEDIUM). 2 MEDIUM items left as noted below.\n\n**Fixes applied:**\n\n1. **HIGH — Command injection** in `validateRuntime`: Added shell metacharacter validation (`; & | \\` $ ( ) { } ! #`) on `testCommand` before passing to `execSync`. Added 3 tests.\n2. **HIGH — Query timeout too short**: `queryTelemetryEvents` was using `HEALTH_TIMEOUT_MS` (3s) — changed to new `QUERY_TIMEOUT_MS` (30s) constant since query responses can be large.\n3. **MEDIUM — Invalid URL crash**: `new URL()` in `queryTelemetryEvents` could throw on malformed endpoint. Wrapped in try/catch returning `fail()`. Added 1 test.\n4. **MEDIUM — Unused parameter smell**: `_projectDir` in `mapEventsToModules` changed to `projectDir` with explicit `void projectDir` and comment.\n\n**Test results:** 2660 tests pass, 0 regressions, 35 tests in runtime-validator (up from 31).\n**Coverage:** 96.46% overall (target: 90%), all 110 files above 80% per-file floor.\n**Build:** Clean.\n**Story status:** Updated to `verifying`.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and fixed:**\n- HIGH: Command injection vulnerability — `execSync(cfg.testCommand)` executed unsanitized user input. Fixed with metacharacter rejection.\n- HIGH: Query timeout of 3 seconds (health timeout reused) caused false failures on large telemetry responses. Fixed with 30s query-specific timeout.\n- MEDIUM: `queryTelemetryEvents` crashed on malformed `queryEndpoint` URL. Fixed with try/catch around `new URL()`.\n- MEDIUM: `_projectDir` unused parameter underscore convention was misleading. Fixed with explicit void.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- `runtime-validator.ts` grew to 212 lines (story aspirational target was 200, hard limit 300). The 12-line increase is justified by security hardening. Not a blocker.\n- `parseLogEvents` silently drops malformed JSON lines. A counter or warning log of dropped lines would improve debuggability in production, but this is acceptable for now.\n- `mapEventsToModules` does substring matching (`event.source.includes(mod)`) which can produce false positives for short module names (e.g., module \"a\" would match source \"database\"). This is a known fuzzy-matching trade-off documented in the story.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- No integration tests with a real VictoriaLogs instance (story explicitly marks AC#1 as `integration-required`). All I/O is mocked. Real integration testing deferred to Story 3.1 audit coordinator.\n- No test for concurrent `validateRuntime` calls (not relevant for CLI, but relevant if used in server context).\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- `saveRuntimeCoverage()` does not persist `ModuleTelemetryEntry[]` (module-level details) to `sprint-state.json`. The audit coordinator (Story 3.1) will need module details for reporting. This gap exists in Story 2.1's persistence function, not in 2.3 itself. Story 3.1 should address it.\n- `config.timeoutMs` is only used for the test subprocess, not propagated to the query timeout. This is a minor inconsistency — the two timeouts serve different purposes but it could confuse callers expecting a single unified timeout.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed. Story passes review."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a119eab07b00fcd0b (use SendMessage with to: 'a119eab07b00fcd0b' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 39229\ntool_uses: 22\nduration_ms: 142348</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c5eaf6a6-ac7c-4707-b82c-6220d711aa9c","uuid":"5d43acba-003d-4619-aa53-d0bad34a2ce7","timestamp":"2026-03-20T06:47:00.355Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/2-3-standalone-runtime-check-audit-mode.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files pass the per-file floor and the overall 90% target. Update the story status to `verifying` when all issues are fixed and coverage passes. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Bugs found and their severity (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW with brief description)\n- Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority items, tech debt)\n- Coverage gaps (files below floor, untested edge cases, areas needing integration tests)\n- Architecture concerns (patterns that don't fit, coupling issues, missing abstractions)\n- Items sent back for re-development (what failed and why)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`","agentId":"a119eab07b00fcd0b","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is the summary of what was done:\n\n**Adversarial review completed** on Story 2.3 (standalone runtime validator). Found and fixed 4 issues (3 HIGH, 1 MEDIUM). 2 MEDIUM items left as noted below.\n\n**Fixes applied:**\n\n1. **HIGH — Command injection** in `validateRuntime`: Added shell metacharacter validation (`; & | \\` $ ( ) { } ! #`) on `testCommand` before passing to `execSync`. Added 3 tests.\n2. **HIGH — Query timeout too short**: `queryTelemetryEvents` was using `HEALTH_TIMEOUT_MS` (3s) — changed to new `QUERY_TIMEOUT_MS` (30s) constant since query responses can be large.\n3. **MEDIUM — Invalid URL crash**: `new URL()` in `queryTelemetryEvents` could throw on malformed endpoint. Wrapped in try/catch returning `fail()`. Added 1 test.\n4. **MEDIUM — Unused parameter smell**: `_projectDir` in `mapEventsToModules` changed to `projectDir` with explicit `void projectDir` and comment.\n\n**Test results:** 2660 tests pass, 0 regressions, 35 tests in runtime-validator (up from 31).\n**Coverage:** 96.46% overall (target: 90%), all 110 files above 80% per-file floor.\n**Build:** Clean.\n**Story status:** Updated to `verifying`.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and fixed:**\n- HIGH: Command injection vulnerability — `execSync(cfg.testCommand)` executed unsanitized user input. Fixed with metacharacter rejection.\n- HIGH: Query timeout of 3 seconds (health timeout reused) caused false failures on large telemetry responses. Fixed with 30s query-specific timeout.\n- MEDIUM: `queryTelemetryEvents` crashed on malformed `queryEndpoint` URL. Fixed with try/catch around `new URL()`.\n- MEDIUM: `_projectDir` unused parameter underscore convention was misleading. Fixed with explicit void.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- `runtime-validator.ts` grew to 212 lines (story aspirational target was 200, hard limit 300). The 12-line increase is justified by security hardening. Not a blocker.\n- `parseLogEvents` silently drops malformed JSON lines. A counter or warning log of dropped lines would improve debuggability in production, but this is acceptable for now.\n- `mapEventsToModules` does substring matching (`event.source.includes(mod)`) which can produce false positives for short module names (e.g., module \"a\" would match source \"database\"). This is a known fuzzy-matching trade-off documented in the story.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- No integration tests with a real VictoriaLogs instance (story explicitly marks AC#1 as `integration-required`). All I/O is mocked. Real integration testing deferred to Story 3.1 audit coordinator.\n- No test for concurrent `validateRuntime` calls (not relevant for CLI, but relevant if used in server context).\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- `saveRuntimeCoverage()` does not persist `ModuleTelemetryEntry[]` (module-level details) to `sprint-state.json`. The audit coordinator (Story 3.1) will need module details for reporting. This gap exists in Story 2.1's persistence function, not in 2.3 itself. Story 3.1 should address it.\n- `config.timeoutMs` is only used for the test subprocess, not propagated to the query timeout. This is a minor inconsistency — the two timeouts serve different purposes but it could confuse callers expecting a single unified timeout.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed. Story passes review."}],"totalDurationMs":142348,"totalTokens":39229,"totalToolUseCount":22,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":306,"cache_read_input_tokens":38013,"output_tokens":909,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":306},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
